General Disciplinary Guidelines:

+ Uncommon and unintentional violations may warrant a verbal and/or
written warning

+ Frequent and intentional violations may lead to suspension and/or
termination

An employee is allowed to request a union representative or witness to attend
all disciplinary meetings. Before approaching an employee suspected of
violating policy, it is advisable to first contact the Human Resource (HR)
department for procedure guidelines

